	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Zepper</b> [ Wed Jan 21, 2009 4:05 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Suggestions:
<br />
<br />1. Checksum (CRC32), PRG+CHR data (no header, of course).
<br />2. Don't allow "free edit" fields, but selectable values, specially for PRG and CHR pages.
<br />3. Check if the ROM size specified in the header (PRG*4000 + CHR*2000) matches the file size. This is important to avoid header conflicts.
<br />4. Ability to add a header into a binary image.
<br />5. Ability to remove the iNES header from a .NES file.
<br />6. External database for proper fixes? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />Anyway, your header editor is simple and easy. This is very important. My suggestions are turned to a ROM fixer, but if this isn't your goal, I understand. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


